# Nuxt.js Frontend Rules — Bunyan

## Directory Structure

```
frontend/
├── app.vue
├── nuxt.config.ts
├── app.config.ts           # Nuxt UI color config
├── assets/css/
├── components/             # common/, project/, workflow/, ecommerce/, dashboard/
├── composables/            # useApi.ts, useAuth.ts, useWorkflow.ts, useDirection.ts
├── layouts/                # default.vue, auth.vue, admin.vue
├── middleware/             # auth.ts, role.ts
├── pages/                  # index.vue, auth/, dashboard/, projects/, shop/, admin/
├── stores/                 # auth.ts, projects.ts, cart.ts, notifications.ts
├── i18n/                   # ar.json, en.json
├── tests/                  # unit/, components/, e2e/
└── nuxt.config.ts
```

## Component Template

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
interface Props {
  title: string;
  status: string;
}

const props = defineProps<Props>();
const emit = defineEmits<{
  update: [value: string];
}>();
</script>

<template>
  <UCard>
    <template #header>
      <h3>{{ props.title }}</h3>
    </template>
    <!-- content -->
  </UCard>
</template>
```

## Design System (MANDATORY)

- **Follow `DESIGN.md`** for visual language: Geist fonts, shadow-as-border, achromatic palette, negative letter-spacing
- See `.cursor/rules/015-design-system.mdc` for quick reference

## Nuxt UI Rules (MANDATORY)

- Always use Nuxt UI components before writing custom HTML
- Use `UDashboardLayout` / `UDashboardSidebar` for app shell
- Use `USteppers` for multi-step flows
- Use `UButton`, `UCard`, `UForm`, `UTable`, `UModal`, etc.
- Configure colors via `app.config.ts` → `ui.colors`
- **Never use Bootstrap classes** — Nuxt UI + Tailwind CSS v4 only
- Install: `npx nuxi@latest module add ui`
- Docs: https://ui.nuxt.com | MCP: https://mcp.nuxt.com

## RTL & Arabic Design (CRITICAL)

- Set `dir="rtl"` on `<html>` element
- Nuxt UI RTL: Tailwind logical properties auto-mirror layout
- Configure in `nuxt.config.ts` → `app.head.htmlAttrs.dir`
- Numbers and dates formatted for Arabic locale
- Nuxt UI icons mirror automatically in RTL context
- All UI strings via `@nuxtjs/i18n` translation files

## API Layer (MANDATORY)

- All API calls via centralized API composable
- Auto-inject Sanctum token
- Handle errors consistently
- Never trust client-supplied authorization data

## RBAC UI Enforcement (MANDATORY)

- Protect routes via Nuxt middleware based on role
- Hide forbidden actions in UI
- Match backend RBAC matrix
- Show role-appropriate dashboards

## State Management

- Pinia stores for: auth, projects, workflow, cart, notifications
- Composables for reusable logic
- No direct API calls in components — use stores/composables

## Form Validation

- VeeValidate for form state management
- Zod schemas for validation rules
- Arabic error messages
- File upload components for reports

## Performance

- Lazy-load routes and heavy components
- Image optimization
- Paginate lists
- Debounce search inputs

## Dashboard Layout by Role

| Role                  | Features                                        |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| Customer              | Projects, payments, orders                      |
| Contractor            | Assigned projects, earnings, withdrawals        |
